70 Existing law requires the driver of a vehicle involved in a crash to take certain
71 actions, which vary depending on whether the crash involves injury or death or
72 attended or unattended property and whether a police officer is present. (NRS
73 484E.020-484E.050) Sections 8-11 of this bill clarify the location-based
74 requirements for the responsibilities of a driver following a crash on a highway or
75 premises to which the public has access. Specifically, section 8 requires the driver
76 of a vehicle involved in such a crash that results only in damage to a vehicle or
77 other property driven or attended by a person to stop and, if the vehicle is
78 obstructing traffic and can be moved safely, move it to a safe location. (NRS
79 484E.020) Section 9 requires the driver of a vehicle involved in such a crash that
80 results in injury, death or damage to attended property to stop, provide certain
81 information, render aid if needed and report the crash to law enforcement under
82 certain circumstances. (NRS 484E.030) Section 10 clarifies that the duties of a
83 driver who is involved in a crash with unattended property apply when the crash
84 occurs on a highway or premises to which the public has access. (NRS 484E.040)
85 Section 11 provides that the duty to report a crash involving unattended property
86 applies when the crash occurs on a highway. (NRS 484E.050)
